The writ of possession shall meet all of the following requirements:
The writ shall be directed to the sheriff;
The writ shall describe the specific property to be seized in accordance with KRS 425.011(2)(c);
The writ shall specify any private place that may be entered to take possession of the property or some part of it; and
The writ shall direct the sheriff to levy on the property pursuant to KRS 425.091 if found and to retain it in his custody until released or sold pursuant to KRS 425.101.
